In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims February 2013 as National African American History Month. He reflects on the dream of equality and fairness that has been a part of America's founding, and acknowledges the struggles that African Americans have faced in realizing this dream. The president emphasizes the importance of honoring the individuals who have fought for freedom and equal rights throughout history. He also encourages public officials, educators, librarians, and all Americans to observe the month with appropriate programs and activities. President Obama concludes by urging everyone to strive towards the example set by those who came before, in order to create a better future for all.